data.title: New Jersey Election Law Enforcement Commission .::. Agent Governmental Application
data.text:
What is ELEC?

Established in 1973‚ ELEC monitors the campaign financing of all elections in the State. Whether the election is for Governor or Mayor‚ member of the Legislature or a City Council‚ candidates and campaign organizations are required to file with the Commission contribution and expenditure reports.

View Historical Information

Address

The New Jersey Election Law Enforcement Commission is located at 25 S. Stockton Street, 5th Floor, Trenton, New Jersey.
